Reasoning: The current formulas in K2:K5 use a case‑insensitive equality (`$A2=$J$2`). The instruction requires a case‑sensitive match, which can be achieved with the `EXACT` function. We will replace each formula with:

```
=IF(EXACT($A{row},$J$2), $B{row} - N($C{row}) - N($E{row}) - N($G{row}), 0)
```

`N()` converts blank cells to 0, satisfying the “blank cells as zeros” requirement. We will keep the number format `"0"` to remove decimals.

After updating the formulas, we will run `recalculate` to evaluate them, reload the workbook with `data_only=True`, and verify that K2:K5 all contain `0`. Finally, we will submit the output spreadsheet path.
Code:
```repl
import os, openpyxl

# Paths
input_path = "/sandbox/input/input_spreadsheet/1_38074_init.xlsx"
output_dir = "/sandbox/output/output_spreadsheet"
output_path = os.path.join(output_dir, "1_38074_init.xlsx")

# Ensure output directory exists
os.makedirs(output_dir, exist_ok=True)

# Load workbook (keep formulas)
wb = openpyxl.load_workbook(input_path, data_only=False)
ws = wb[wb.sheetnames[0]]  # first sheet

# Update formulas in K2:K5 with case‑sensitive EXACT and N() for blanks
for row in range(2, 6):  # rows 2‑5 inclusive
    cell = ws.cell(row=row, column=11)  # Column K = 11
    formula = f"=IF(EXACT($A{row},$J$2),$B{row}-N($C{row})-N($E{row})-N($G{row}),0)"
    cell.value = formula
    cell.number_format = "0"   # no decimals

# Save the workbook to the output location
wb.save(output_path)

# Recalculate formulas so LibreOffice can compute them
recalc_result = await recalculate(output_path)
print("Recalculate result:", recalc_result)

# Load the workbook with data_only=True to read evaluated values
wb_check = openpyxl.load_workbook(output_path, data_only=True)
ws_check = wb_check[wb_check.sheetnames[0]]
values = [ws_check.cell(row=r, column=11).value for r in range(2, 6)]
print("Calculated K2:K5 values after recalc:", values)
```
